One hundred and twelve patents in Supplementary Table 1 describe methods for treating viral infections: cytomegalovirus, hepatitis B, hepatitis C, herpes simplex,
HIV, human papilloma virus, human T-cell leukemia virus, influenza B, polyomavirus, varicella zoster and Zika virus. An often- used strategy is the ex vivo modification
