‘There are several approaches for determining the ecological consequences of GM crops. Examples include extrapolations from experience with comparable traits or with other crop varieties that are in some or all ways ‘equivalent’, laboratory and field experiments, experience of GM crops, and ecological modelling. In practice it is usually necessary to use a number of these methods in combination.
